<span id="fn_1336"></span>[48:1337](2080059.htm#fr_1336.md) <span
id="vii.xxx-p38.2"></span>

<span id="vii.xxx-p39"></span> The Benedictine version for <span
class="Greek"><span id="vii.xxx-p39.1"></span>τὰς τιμὰς τοῦ
κυρίου</span> is *honorem quem Dominus tribuit Spiritui*.  The reading
of one <span class="c14"><span id="vii.xxx-p39.2"></span>ms.</span> is
<span class="Greek"><span id="vii.xxx-p39.3"></span>τὰς φωνάς</span>. 
There is authority for either sense of the genitive with <span
class="Greek"><span id="vii.xxx-p39.4"></span>τιμή</span>, *i.e.* the
honours *due to the Lord* or *paid by the Lord*.

